article.headline: DePaul 75, N. Illinois 52
article.story: DeKALB, Ill. -- Cleveland Melvin led a balanced attack with 19 points as DePaul used a dominating second-half performance to top Northern Illinois 75-52 on Wednesday night. The Blue Demons (7-3) won their third straight as Brandon Young scored 16, while Jeremiah Kelly added 15 and Moses Morgan 11. Tim Toler led the Huskies (0-9) with 18 points and 13 rebounds. The Blue Demons led only 28-25 at intermission but then launched a decisive run in the second half. Five players scored as DePaul turned a 33-32 deficit into a 49-33 lead by the 13:49 mark. The Blue Demons closed the game with a 14-4 run, including six straight points from Melvin.
